This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with scene text detection in natural images. It also involves the use of convolutional neural networks, which is a common technique in computer vision. 

It could also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as text detection is a crucial step in many information retrieval tasks such as document analysis and OCR. 

The paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as semantic information extraction from text regions, which could place it in the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. 

The use of customized convolutional networks and in-network fusions suggests that the paper could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper involves the use of multi-scale and multi-shape text detection, which could place it in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category as it deals with the analysis of visual content in images.
